Display Minimum Salary, Maximum Salary and Average Salary with 3 sepearate columns

Take a String like "GOOD MORNING" display only "GOOD", length of "MORNING". Join a word "afternoon" with "GOOD"
 which should be taken from "GOOD MORNING" and display result in all CAPS.
 
 SELECT 
    MIN(salary) AS minimum_salary,
    MAX(salary) AS maximum_salary,
    AVG(salary) AS average_salary
FROM employees;

SELECT 
    SUBSTRING('GOOD MORNING', 1, 4) AS first_word,
    LENGTH(SUBSTRING('GOOD MORNING', 6, 7)) AS length_of_second_word,
    UPPER(CONCAT(SUBSTRING('GOOD MORNING', 1, 4), ' afternoon')) AS final_result;
